      <sectiondef kind="func">
      <memberdef kind="function" id="group___graphics_utilities_1gad6feebe7c24c843d6ba0568a2ea47434" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>typedef</type>
        <definition>typedef __attribute__</definition>
        <argsstring>((deprecated(&quot;Use OpenXR APIs.&quot;))) struct MLGraphicsImportedMediaSurface</argsstring>
        <name>__attribute__</name>
        <param>
          <type>(deprecated(&quot;Use OpenXR APIs.&quot;))</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Handles to and information about an imported surface. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Import a surface as a VkImage from a media api handle.</para>
<para>Returns a list of required VkDevice extension names.</para>
<para><xrefsect id="deprecated_1_deprecated000048"><xreftitle>Deprecated</xreftitle><xrefdescription><para>Deprecated since 1.6.0. Scheduled for removal. </para>
</xrefdescription></xrefsect></para>
<para>Populated by #MLGraphicsImportVkImageFromMediaHandle. Provides all information, necessary for creating a VkImageView and VkSampler for the imported surface.</para>
<para>Refer to the Vulkan specification&apos;s equivalent parameters in VkAndroidHardwareBufferFormatPropertiesANDROID. Also refer to usage of VkExternalFormatANDROID and VkSamplerYcbcrConversionCreateInfo.</para>
<para><xrefsect id="deprecated_1_deprecated000051"><xreftitle>Deprecated</xreftitle><xrefdescription><para>Deprecated since 1.6.0. Scheduled for removal. </para>
</xrefdescription></xrefsect></para>
<para>If out_required_extension_properties is NULL then the number of required extension is returned in out_extension_property_count. Otherwise, out_extension_property_count must point to a variable set to the number of elements in the out_required_extension_properties array, and on return the variable is overwritten with the number of strings actually written to out_required_extension_properties.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="out">out_required_extension_properties</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Either NULL or a pointer to an array of VkExtensionProperties. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="out">out_extension_property_count</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A pointer to an integer related to the number of extensions required or queried.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<parameterlist kind="retval"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>MLResult_InvalidParam</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The query failed due to an invalid parameter. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>MLResult_Ok</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The list of extensions or number of required extensions was returned successfully.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<xrefsect id="permissions_1_permissions000311"><xreftitle>Required Permissions</xreftitle><xrefdescription><para>None </para>
</xrefdescription></xrefsect></para>
<para><xrefsect id="deprecated_1_deprecated000052"><xreftitle>Deprecated</xreftitle><xrefdescription><para>Deprecated since 1.6.0. Scheduled for removal. </para>
</xrefdescription></xrefsect></para>
<para>Creates VkImage and VkDeviceMemory objects refrencing a surface referred to by a handle obtained from a media API. The resulting image will be owned by the VkDevice provided.This VkDevice must be created with the extensions specified by MLGraphicsEnumerateRequiredVkDeviceExtensionsForMediaHandleImport enabled. This call does not depend on a Graphics Client and can be used independent of other graphics APIs.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">vulkan_logical_device</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The Vulkan logical device to use for resource creation. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">media_handle</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The media api handle referring to the surface to import. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="out">out_imported_surface_info</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A struct containing the resulting resource handles and information for sampler creation.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<parameterlist kind="retval"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>MLResult_InvalidParam</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Import was not performed due to an invalid parameter. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>MLResult_Ok</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Surface was imported successfully. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>MLResult_UnspecifiedFailure</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Import was not performed due to an unknown error.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<xrefsect id="permissions_1_permissions000312"><xreftitle>Required Permissions</xreftitle><xrefdescription><para>None </para>
</xrefdescription></xrefsect></para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>The VkImage bound to the imported surface.</para>
<para>The VkDevice memory representing the imported surface.</para>
<para>The Vulkan format corresponding to the imported surface’s format, or VK_FORMAT_UNDEFINED if there isn’t an equivalent Vulkan format.</para>
<para>An implementation-defined external format identifier for use with VkExternalFormatANDROID.</para>
<para>Describes the capabilities of this external format.</para>
<para>The component swizzle that should be used in VkSamplerYcbcrConversionCreateInfo.</para>
<para>Suggested color model to use in the VkSamplerYcbcrConversionCreateInfo.</para>
<para>Suggested numerical value range to use in VkSamplerYcbcrConversionCreateInfo.</para>
<para>Suggested X chroma offset to use in VkSamplerYcbcrConversionCreateInfo.</para>
<para>Suggested Y chroma offset to use in VkSamplerYcbcrConversionCreateInfo.</para>
        </inbodydescription>
